@pklinef @rzwiefel I'm talking specifically about letting blueprint handle the exception instead of us since we can't do anything more meaningful than log. I don't see the point of making the query logic harder to read with that kind of payoff. I think the DI container should handle default cases like this.
Seems like we can propagate FailsafeException and it'll work fine.
